sentences: Lucca Quiñones was born in Ponce, Puerto Rico on 10 April 1946.
In June 2020, their eldest son died of complications due to diabetes.
Throughout the 1950s, Lucca remained active as a musician.
His first opportunity to showcase his talents came in 1976 when he co-produced La Sonora Ponceña's album, Musical Conquest/Conquista Musical, with Louie Ramirez.
In 1976, he replaced pianist Larry Harlow in the Fania All-Stars.
Lucca reached a professional high in 1979.
Lucca also recorded a solo piano album, Latin Jazz, in 1993.
In 2014, Lucca and La Sonora Ponceña played at Lehman Center for the Performing Arts in New York to commemorate their 60-year anniversary.

A month after he enrolled in the school, he performed a classical piece on a local radio station.

Performing with La Sonora Ponceña at the age of eight, he made his recording debut three years later, when the group accompanied bolero vocalists Felipe Rodriguez and Davilita on their album, Al Compas De Las Sonoras.
Two years later, he produced the group's album, Explorando, on his own.
The same year, he performed on an album, Habana Jam, along with the Fania All-Stars, which was recorded during a concert in Cuba.
